[1] USA: Texas quarantine over
Date: 19 Oct 2014
Source: NY Times [edited]
http://www.nytimes.com/2014/10/20/us/ceo-of-texas-hospital-group-at-center-of-ebola-scare-apologizes-for-mistakes.html?_r=0
[This is the correct URL (updated 20 Oct 2014) in spite of the name! - Mod.JW]


At least one chapter of the Ebola saga neared a close Sun [19 Oct 2014], as most of the dozens of people who had direct or indirect contact here with D, the Liberian man who died of Ebola, were told by officials that they were no longer at risk of contracting the disease.

D's fiance, who nursed him in their cramped apartment while he suffered from diarrhea and who was put under state-ordered quarantine, was set to be declared Ebola-free by officials at the end of Sunday [19 Oct 2014]. So, too, were the paramedics who drove [the patient] to a hospital and health care workers who drew or processed his blood. And a mandatory quarantine was lifted for a homeless man who later rode in the same ambulance as D before it was disinfected.

The 21-day monitoring period ended on Sunday and Mon [19-20 Oct 2014] for nearly all the roughly 50 people. It concludes as federal health officials are tightening the guidelines for the protective gear worn by health care workers treating Ebola patients.

[byline: Manny Fernandez & Kevin Sack]

