******
[2] USA: Another recovered patient discharged
Date: 20 Oct 2014
Source: AP [edited]
http://hosted2.ap.org/APDEFAULT/bbd825583c8542898e6fa7d440b9febc/Article_2014-10-20-US-MED--Emory%20Ebola%20Patient/id-f226daafc0114749b2e071dc86ef0709


The unidentified Ebola patient who has been treated in Atlanta since early September [2014] has been released. Emory University Hospital officials said on Mon [20 Oct 2014] that the man was released on Sun [19 Oct 2014], after he was determined to be free of the virus and no threat to the public. The man is a doctor who had been working in an Ebola treatment center in Sierra Leone when he tested positive for the disease. He was taken to Emory on 9 Sep [2014]. The hospital never identified the man, in keeping with his family's wishes for privacy.

Emory is one of 4 US hospitals with specialized treatment units for people with dangerous infectious diseases.

[byline: Mike Stobbe]

