[3] USA: prevention -- military to train medical support team for home deployment
Date: 19 Oct 2014
Source: Politico [edited]
http://www.politico.com/story/2014/10/ebola-defense-department-112014.html


The military is establishing a 30-person expeditionary medical support team to assist medical professionals in the US in treating Ebola cases, the Pentagon said on Sun [19 Oct 2014]. Pentagon press secretary Rear Admiral John Kirby said defense secretary Chuck Hagel had instructed the chief of US Northern Command to prepare and train the team of "20 critical care nurses, 5 doctors trained in infectious disease, and 5 trainers in infectious disease protocols." Starting within the next week or so, the team will receive as many as 7 days of specialized training at Fort Sam Houston, Texas, Kirby added. Then, they'll be prepared to deploy to locations in the United States, but they won't be sent overseas, he said.

[byline: Marjorie Censer]

